                            <comment id="17402743" author="rfscholte" created="Sun, 22 Aug 2021 08:18:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Will be solved with the next version of plexus-java.&lt;br/&gt;
However, keep in mind that the combination of static + transitive is  valid (javac and javadoc understand it), but also very awkward. By saying static you say it is only required at compile time and not at runtime.&lt;br/&gt;
By saying transitive you say that project requiring this module will automatically get the requirement as well.&lt;br/&gt;
So with static transitive the module is optional, but the project using is will get it anyway during compilation, that&apos;s kind of weird, right?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
